      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S ALL FIRE (2) looks close to another win after finishing second last time (29.80) at this track. Has never been out of the money in nine starts this course and distance. Has a strong record from this draw, notching two wins and two minor placings from four starts. Sure to be about the mark. WINSOME RAMBO (1) jumped quickly from wide out to score (25.20) two back then drew the fence last time but settled off pace and could manage only a 8 length 5th at Q Lakeside (25.43). Should be thereabouts. BEAUTIFUL CHILD (4) has an excellent record over this journey having never missed the placings in four starts, including three wins. Comes off a (29.61) win last time, scoring by 2.5 lengths in a Restricted WIN over 520m at this track. Suited here and expected to run well. REMEMBER BRUCE (3) justified the favourite's tag last time and another big run is on the cards.",
